form_values.2d29: Hand excavation of top soil revealed a secondary sub surface wall. The Japanese knotweed appears to be contained by the outer wall. New jk shoots are emerging.  The knotweed appears to be contained to a large extent in a brick and concrete gully.

form_values.2d29: No re growth for two years according to client
Muckaway. Groundworkers had added some extra to the stockpile (not a lot) had to pull out litter and concrete & blocks they’d put there. Swept up and checked area prior to grab leaving site.

Excavated along area of previous known infestation, down the clay and exposed clay lawn side of patio. Pulled brick wall foundation and exposed clay underneath patio. No sign of there being well established widespread root system present, found rhizome in initial lawn scrape.

Notes:- 

1. JK host materials stockpiled directly onto concrete in garage area as no ply sheets supplied as requested. Spoke to groundworker / builder on the phone who said this was client decision and wasn’t bothered that the concrete will get marked up when the stockpile is collected by grab tomorrow. 

2. Prior to leaving site advised groundworker they can bulk up the stockpile with clay (no topsoil / bricks / concrete) to help assist client with cost as it’s load rate. He said he didn’t think he would get any footings dug as no ply onsite to shutter the excavations. Grab is booked for 8am in morning.

other_values: Builder didn’t have plant machinery onsite.
